<tr bgcolor="#7EB4FA">
<td valign="top" width="20%"><font face="verdana,trebuchet,sans-serif" color="black" style="font-size: 11px"><b>NicktheLemming</b>
<br>22 October 2003</font></td><td width="80%"><font><b>Looks good to me :-)</b>
<br>
<p>I especially like the look of the locations, in particular the hotspots, and the Passions book. I'm a little perturbed about adding some new material to the old books - how much will be new, and will you be adding the new material to the website for free download for those of us that have the originals if there isn't much new stuff?<p></p>Also, do you have a rough timeline for when you're going to start releasing books, and what we can expect to see within the next year or so? Which books are currently being worked on, for instance?</p>
</font></td>
</tr>
</table>
<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0" width="100%">
<tr bgcolor="#A0D5FF">
<td valign="top" width="20%"><font face="verdana,trebuchet,sans-serif" color="black" style="font-size: 11px"><b>James Flowers</b>
<br>22 October 2003</font></td><td width="80%"><font><b>Looks good to me :-)</b>
<br>
<p>Hi Nick,<p></p>Thanks for the feedback. We're not sure whether the new material will be made available as a free download as yet. Too early to say, but those reservations are already noted, and we will seriously consider it if it's likely to be a necessary item for existing First Edition gamers.<p></p>We have a timeline for release which we'll share as soon as we've ratified it. There's a lot of work going on in that space. Focus at present is to get the web site into shape and the promotional materials and free stuff up.<p></p>We will put an announcement up as changes occur.<p></p>Hope this helps,<br>JAMES FLOWERS<br>Line Developer, RedBrick Limited</p>
</font></td>
</tr>
</table>
